															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/monteparnas" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2926286); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2926286&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227428" alt="Monteparnas" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2926286)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/monteparnas" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2926286); return false;" >Monteparnas</a></span> <span class="odate time_1558259652 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">19 May 2019 09:54</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4254156">
									

<p>I can see the goal was to get some closure for SCP-2106. But the thing is, I didn't got any.</p>
<p>The tale of the bird-woman really has left me wanting. She had some really bad experiences there, and in the end she and the Foundation were kind of trying to re-establish contact.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>But here what I see is a WWS employee working with a super-powered terrorist group that causes major destruction and kill several people just to let the woman&#8230; whatever. Because at no point was I convinced that she wanted anything resembling that. She didn't seemed to want to die, she didn't seemed to want to go to any particular place. Even the idea that she wanted freedom on a broader sense was implied far more by other people than her.</p>
<p>Why the WWS liaison did any of this? It isn't hard to think a reason, actually isn't hard to think several reasons, but none is actually given or implied. Why the talking crow is doing whatever it is doing? Why it mingles with 3466? Why it goes so destructive?</p>
<p>More simpler than that, if the Foundation just accepted to deliver 2106 to WWS, why it attacked the convoy at all!? There was no reason, the liaison could give a better life to 2106 at WWS, or free her from there, that would be a lot easier. And certainly hurt the relationship between Foundation and WWS less than a terrorist attack synchronized with their request that caused severe damage to expensive equipment and the loss of several agents lives.</p>
<p>On a similar note, why the agent didn't pulled the trigger against <strong>the bird</strong>!? I mean, as tough as the crow talked, it was an easy target right there to do a lot more for the Foundation. Was the crow in control of the attacking party? It seemed at least an important asset to a group that just attacked the Foundation directly.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<br />
<em>As a courtesy to our readers on mobile devices, please collapse long posts. ~Zyn</em>
<p>Sorry, but that story ended up being a complete mess to me. It says nothing except that every character was careless and acted with too little motivation. And even the idea that 2106's condition didn't changed significantly since 2011 seemed off.</p>

							</div>

								
